      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;mental-health&#34;&gt;Mental health&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Expressing the reality of mental health as a teenager is incredibly difficult.
You’re expected to have it all figured out while your brain is still under construction.
Throwing a relationship into that mix? That’s a whole different level of complexity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Honestly, trying to manage family expectations, a girlfriend’s needs, and a
social life all at once is a genuine art form. Add a full day of staring at
a screen, losing yourself in lines of code, and you’re running on empty before
the day is even half over.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
